# Secrets — never commit. The dashboard doesn't need keys; fetchers read
# keys.local.json locally or env vars (in CI: GitHub secrets).
keys.local.json

# ADMIN_PASSCODE (gates the public dashboard's run/holdout controls) lives
# here for local testing only — the real one belongs in Streamlit Cloud's
# app secrets UI, never in the repo.
.streamlit/secrets.toml

# /cso security reports — local audit trail, not repo content.
.gstack/

# Local caches and artifacts (regenerable; panel.pkl is refetched on demand)
data_cache/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store

# Eval scratch
research-methodology/evals/

# Internal working documents — the repo is the product, these are the diary
# (build log + living spec). They stay local; repo docs = README only.
#
# This rule is deliberately broad: session notes, run reports, and status
# write-ups are build history, not product. Anything durable belongs in README
# or in a code comment where it will actually be read. If a new doc is genuinely
# for someone cloning the repo, add it explicitly with `git add -f`.
scratchpad.md
market-research-agent-spec.md
*_NOTES.md
*_TEST.md
*_DUMP.md
*_REPORT.md

# Archived pre-launch test data (journal reset backups) — not functional
# product code, kept locally as a record only.
archive/

# Per-row out-of-sample scoring data. 17MB PER ITERATION since the universe
# grew to 166 tickers (86,269 rows each) — 156MB of a 238MB repo, growing
# permanently with every run. The deployed dashboard needs ~660KB total to
# render everything (journal.db + feature.py + transcripts + team
# conversations); these CSVs power ONLY the "download the exact rows" box,
# which dashboard.py already guards with an .exists() check and degrades
# gracefully without. Kept on disk locally so that feature still works for you;
# regenerate for any iteration by re-running its feature through the evaluator.
proposals/*/oos_rows.csv

# Crashed/partial runs parked for inspection — no journal entry, not product.
proposals/_partial/

# Generated artifacts: run logs and the agent-context dump (regenerate on demand).
logs_multiagent_run.log
AGENT_CONTEXT_DUMP.md
